# Define the specific value you're interested in
specific_value = 'wt_ut_br2_tr1'

# Create a Boolean mask where True corresponds to rows in 'adata.obs['Sample_ID']' that match 'specific_value'
mask = adata.obs['Sample_ID'] == specific_value

# Use the mask to extract the corresponding rows from 'adata.obsm['X_pca']'
filtered_pca = adata.obsm['X_pca'][mask]
# filtered_pca.shape

model = mellon.DensityEstimator()
log_density = model.fit_predict(filtered_pca)

predictor = model.predict(adata.obsm['X_pca'])
# predictor
# predictor.shape

adata.obs["wt_ut1_log_density"] = predictor
adata.obs["wt_ut1_log_density_clipped"] = np.clip(
    predictor, *np.quantile(predictor, [0.05, 1])
)

sc.pl.scatter(
    adata, color=["wt_ut1_log_density", "wt_ut1_log_density_clipped"], basis="umap"
)
